# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  STEP-BY-STEP DEPLOYMENT:
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  1. Create a GitHub repository
#     - Upload all your HTML files + netlify folder + netlify.toml
#
#  2. Sign up at netlify.com (free)
#     - Click "Add new site" → "Import an existing project"
#     - Connect to your GitHub repo
#     - Build command: (leave blank)
#     - Publish directory: .
#     - Click Deploy
#
#  3. Add your NVIDIA API key:
#     - Go to Site Settings → Environment Variables
#     - Click "Add a variable"
#     - Key:   NVIDIA_API_KEY
#     - Value: nvapi-your-actual-key-here
#     - Save and Redeploy
#
#  4. Install the openai npm package for functions:
#     Create a package.json in your root:
#     {
#       "dependencies": {
#         "openai": "^4.0.0"
#       }
#     }
#
#  5. Your site will be live at: https://your-site.netlify.app
#     - qa_tutorial.html  → https://your-site.netlify.app/qa_tutorial.html
#     - painmap.html      → https://your-site.netlify.app/painmap.html
